    ('Capital',
      'Capital is production and productivity, the potential for action and the urge to act.
      Capital is resources - human, natural and otherwise. Capital is row, unformed and unorganised:
      useless on its own, nothing can be done without it. Capital serves no master but itself,
      just as those who serve only Capital serve only themselves. Capital is the cake and the knife
      that cuts it. Will you grab for a slice or settle for the crumbs?',
