        ('The Consumer',
          'The Consumer may represent the protagonist of the narrative, but also
          stands for the urge to transcend the status quo, to act without forethought.
          The Consumer is innocent, and occasionally outright foolish. The Consumer
          is - as yet - unbruised by the world into which they enthusiastically set off.
          While there can be bravery in The Consumers innocence: a willingless to changeor
          to be changed, bad things happen to innocents abroad...and they may be poor
          company when the chips are down.',
